### English Title:
Russian Foreign Minister: WTO "Paralyzed" by US Administrations

### English Text Summary:
Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov stated that the World Trade Organization (WTO) is "paralyzed" due to successive US administrations and called for peaceful agreements on tariffs between the US and other countries. Speaking at the Antalya Diplomatic Forum in Turkey, he noted that the ongoing trade war is likely to change many aspects of international relations, with several countries expressing a desire to negotiate with the US. Lavrov emphasized that a peaceful resolution satisfying both parties is essential. He also mentioned that the WTO has been ineffective for many years, lacking global trust. Earlier in the week, the Kremlin indicated it was closely monitoring global oil prices, which fell following President Donald Trump's decision to impose high tariffs on numerous countries.

